quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  100,10,"and the secrets of the hearts are laid bare (and examined)?",footnotes:182822:1
  101,1,"The Calamity!",footnotes:182824:1
  101,2,"What is the Calamity?"
  101,3,"And what do you know what the Calamity is?"
  101,4,"On that Day human beings shall be like scattered moths,"
  101,5,"and the mountains shall be like fluffs of carded wool in varying colours.",footnotes:182825:1
  101,6,"Then he whose scales weigh heavier",footnotes:182826:1
  101,7,"shall have a blissful life;"
  101,8,"but he whose scales weigh lighter,",footnotes:182827:1
  101,9,"his shall be the deep pit for a dwelling.",footnotes:182828:1
  101,10,"And what do you know what that is?"
  102,1,"The craving for ever-greater worldly gains and to excel others in that regard keeps you occupied",footnotes:182830:1
  102,2,"until you reach your graves.",footnotes:182831:1
  102,3,"Nay, you will soon come to know;",footnotes:182832:1
  102,4,"nay, again, you shall soon come to know."
  102,5,"Nay, would that you knew with certainty of knowledge (what your attitude will lead to, you would never have acted the way you do)."
  102,6,"You will surely end up seeing Hell;"
  102,7,"again, you shall most certainly end up seeing it with absolute certainty."
  102,8,"Then, on that Day, you will be called to account for all the bounties you enjoyed.",footnotes:182833:1